sub_title: Deputy Head of Mission @ Embassy of Chile | Political Science, Diplomacy
summary:
With over 20 years of experience in international relations, diplomacy, and public diplomacy, I currently serve as the Deputy Head of Mission at the Embassy of Chile to the Netherlands, and as a Bilateral Relations Analyst at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Chile. My core competencies include government affairs, NGOs, civil society, and international politics.

My mission is to foster and strengthen the relations between Chile and other countries, especially in the areas of culture, human rights, and environmental issues. I have contributed to the development and implementation of various bilateral and multilateral agreements, projects, and initiatives, working with diverse stakeholders and partners. I hold a Master's degree in International Politics from the Universidad de Santiago de Chile, and I have studied Japanese language and culture at the Japan Foundation Japanese-Language Institute. I am passionate about promoting the values and interests of Chile and its people, as well as enhancing the cooperation and dialogue among different nations and cultures. I am also committed to learning and adapting to new challenges and opportunities in the dynamic and complex global context.
